         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melb. bot.Garden ¶ 27/2/70 ¶  ¶ Let me in first instance, dear Dr Hooker, offer my best gratulation to your long &amp; well deserved honor of the Companionship of the Bath. ¶  May you long live to enjoy t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.02.27a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, ff. 421-2.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melb. bot.Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27/2/70</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me in first instance, dear Dr Hooker, offer my best gratulation to your long &amp; well deserved honor of the Companionship of the Bath.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hooker was appointed a Companion of the Order of the Bath on 6 November 1869 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">London Gazette</seg>, 9 November 1869, p. 5975). See Lucas (2013a) for a discusion of Hooker's attitude to this and other honours.</p>
               </note> May you long live to enjoy this mark of approbation from the throne.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will be impossible to send a living <name key="Loranthus">Loranthus</name> or viscum, as the sap of a comparatively small movable plant would surely get exhausted by the parasite on the 3 months voyage and both would die. But would it be wise to grow the <name key="Loranthus">Loranthus</name>? It is sure to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">kill</hi>
               </seg> anything it is put on.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Hooker to M, 10 December 1869 (in this edition as 69-12-10a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I always congratulate the Tasmanians on the absense of Misletoes in their island. You might <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">easily</hi>
               </seg> raise them from seed. But why not rather grow the Terrestrial <name key="Nuytsia">Nuytsia</name> &amp; <name key="Atkinsonia">Atkinsonia</name>? Both can be raised readily from seed! in an ordinary pot ful earth; nor does the seed soon lose its vitality.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am grateful for the Acorns &amp; other seeds you again so attentively sent</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If my <name key="Mesembryanthemum%20tegens">Mesembryanthemum tegens</name> is the real M. debile,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Hooker to M, 31 December 1869 (in this edition as 69-12-31b).</p>
               </note> then Sonders quotation of the latter under M. reptans is wrong, as it is <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">yellow</hi>
               </seg> flowered[.]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M described the flowers of his new <seg style="font-style: italic; ">M. tegens</seg> as 'pallidius roseis' (pale pink) in B66.10.01, p. 157, but in Harvey &amp; Sonder (1859-65), vol. 2, p. 407, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">M. reptens</seg>, under which <seg style="font-style: italic; ">M. debile </seg>is synonomized, is said to have yellow flowers.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope poor Dr Ward will not turn himself in his coffin, if he hears your new appellation of his cases, however applicable it is.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Hooker to M, 8 December 1869, in which the topics discussed in the remainder of the letter also appear.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr O'Shanesy at Rockhampton has a small Nursery of plants.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have several thousand <name key="Cinchona">Cinchona</name>s growing under some slight brush shelter but intend to take them to the Ranges, whenever we are settled calmly down in politics to commence forest culture. In our warm fern-tree vallies they ought to do quite well. They will even stand a slight frost, provided the frost is not combined with cutting winds.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is strange that <name key="Eucalyptus%20polyanthemus">Eucalyptus polyanthemus</name> should bear the English winter, since it is a species from the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">warmer</hi>
               </seg> parts of Australia.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
